  <main class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8">

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-4">Intent</h2>
      <p>Guarantee <strong>exactly-once</strong> execution for external side effects (HTTP calls, emails, SMS, webhooks) while allowing <strong>at-least-once</strong> retry for internal operations (database writes, middleware notifications). Achieve this by introducing a persistent "in-flight" state that acts as a transactional barrier.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-4">Also Known As</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
        <li>Transactional Guard State</li>
        <li>Pending Execution Marker</li>
        <li>Two-Phase Action State</li>
        <li>In-Progress Lock Pattern</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-4">Motivation</h2>
      <p>Many systems must perform an external operation (like sending an SMS) exactly once, but a failure after that operation may require retrying internal logic (database updates, monitoring events). Traditional transaction boundaries do not fit: rolling back the transaction would re-trigger the external call.</p>
      <p>The In-Flight State Pattern solves this by separating the workflow into <strong>three explicit phases</strong> with isolated transactional behavior.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-4">Structure</h2>
      <p>The system transitions through three phases:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
        <li><strong>Phase 1 ‚Äî Guard:</strong> Move from INITIAL ‚Üí IN_FLIGHT with <code>REQUIRES_NEW</code> to commit the state immediately.</li>
        <li><strong>Phase 2 ‚Äî External Action:</strong> Perform the side effect (HTTP/SMS). Never retried automatically.</li>
        <li><strong>Phase 3 ‚Äî Finalization:</strong> Update internal state and send notifications. Fully retryable.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-4">Participants</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
        <li><strong>Domain Entity</strong>: Holds the persistent state (INITIAL ‚Üí IN_FLIGHT ‚Üí DONE).</li>
        <li><strong>Guard Service</strong>: Moves the entity into IN_FLIGHT using an isolated transaction.</li>
        <li><strong>External Client</strong>: Performs the non-idempotent external call.</li>
        <li><strong>Finalizer Service</strong>: Writes final status, retryable.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-4">Consequences</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
        <li>‚úÖ Prevents duplicate external calls</li>
        <li>‚úÖ Allows robust retry of internal logic</li>
        <li>‚úÖ Crash-safe thanks to early commit</li>
        <li>‚ö†Ô∏è Requires a cleanup job for stuck IN_FLIGHT rows</li>
        <li>‚ö†Ô∏è Slightly more complex state machine</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-4">Java Example</h2>
      <pre class="bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded p-4 overflow-x-auto text-sm"><code>@Transactional(propagation = REQUIRES_NEW)
public void markInFlight(Long id) {
    repo.updateStatus(id, IN_FLIGHT, INITIAL);
}

public SmsResult sendOnce(Appointment item) {
    return smsClient.send(item); // never retried
}

@Retryable(maxAttempts = 3)
@Transactional
public void finalize(Long id, SmsResult result) {
    repo.updateStatus(id, DONE, result.reference());
    middleware.notify(result);
}</code></pre>
    </section>

  </main>

